User Stories

As a potential client I want to be able to load a CT scan into the model

As a potential client I want to be able to get a segmented and labelled image of the CT scan displayed showing the different parts of the CT scan like bone, air, white matter, ventricles etc.

As a potential client I want to be able to see a segmented CT scan which could be used to target specific areas of the brain for safer surgery procedures.

As a potential client I want this application to accept different CT scan sizes and resolutions.

As a potential client I want this to be a model with a basic interface which can be easily integrated into other apps like a mobile app

Semantic Brain Segmentation

A software development venture comprised of the intellectual property and knowledge of Andrew Abumoussa, MD as well as the technical expertise of our team of developers.

With the development of this software we hope to contribute to the medical community at large by providing more modern-day post-processing abilities to life-saving technologies such as MRI and CT scans.

We intend to use machine learning as a tool to process radiographic images and classify their contents into useful, identifiable features that might aid in a medical professional’s understanding of their patient.

Rules

For Software Development

-Use Github for code collaboration and version control

-Comment code so everyone can understand your parts 

-Maintain appropriate documentation (commit messages, packages, var. names)

-Design or map out all features before beginning to code

-Verify that the code is working before committing it to github

-Warn the team before committing code to prevent overwriting

General

-Respond to all messages from team members or client in a prompt manner

-Attend all mandatory meetings

-Communicate via text group chat, in person, or over zoom.

-Inform group about absences ahead of time

-Meet at least once weekly with the team and coach

-Strive to be early in meeting deadlines and attending meetings
